133
00:07:49.856 --> 00:07:53.196
So it's sort of a two-edged sword that we're balancing in that.

134
00:07:53.736 --> 00:07:57.596
And irradiated tumor cells also can generally release

135
00:07:57.696 --> 00:08:01.436
signals to neighboring cells for

136
00:08:01.816 --> 00:08:05.806
apoptosis or other responses. So the fundamental

137
00:08:05.836 --> 00:08:08.316
hypothesis is that immunological benefits of

138
00:08:08.356 --> 00:08:10.366
radioligand therapy,

139
00:08:11.176 --> 00:08:13.866
can these be enhanced through radioisotope selection,

140
00:08:15.036 --> 00:08:18.586
emission type, half-life, dosimetry, timing of

141
00:08:18.636 --> 00:08:22.446
adjacent immunotherapy? There's a lot of things that we can do with

142
00:08:22.476 --> 00:08:26.366
molecular targeted radiotheranostics above and beyond traditional

143
00:08:26.396 --> 00:08:28.276
external beam. And indeed,

